other_tests.procedure_name: CT Abdomen and Pelvis with Contrast
other_tests.findings: Appendix distended up to 8 mm with hyperemia of the wall and an appendicolith at the base; surrounding fluid present. Normal findings for liver, spleen, kidneys, adrenal glands, pancreas, gallbladder, stomach, and small bowel. Right ovary shows a peripherally enhancing hemorrhagic follicle, and left ovary is unremarkable.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Intrauterine device seen within the uterus, similar in position compared to prior, with relatively less myometrium seen adjacent to the right arm, better characterized by ultrasound.
